Looking through the code a bit to get a better understanding of the entire flow. Found this:

https://github.com/protolambda/zrnt/blob/master/eth2/beacon/block_processing/block_attestation.go#L67

```golang
	if targetEpoch == state.Epoch() {
		state.CurrentEpochAttestations = append(state.CurrentEpochAttestations, pendingAttestation)
	} else {
		state.PreviousEpochAttestations = append(state.CurrentEpochAttestations, pendingAttestation)
}
```
should probably be 
```golang
	if targetEpoch == state.Epoch() {
		state.CurrentEpochAttestations = append(state.CurrentEpochAttestations, pendingAttestation)
	} else {
		state.PreviousEpochAttestations = append(state.PreviousEpochAttestations, pendingAttestation)
}
```
Also, I'm curious.. The call to `ProcessAttestation` will modify the `state` when processing attestations, and if the last attestation fails, the previous ones in the block will be added to the current/previous anyway. 

```golang
		if err := ProcessAttestation(state, &attestation); err != nil {
			return err
}
```
EDIT: ah, I guess that is ok, because the error will cause the entire state to be thrown away.

And thirdly, since you're just appending attestations, what is to prevent the same attestation from getting added again and again?

